  "prompt": "What type of doctor treats hemorrhoids? How is it treated?",
  "response": "Hemorrhoids are typically treated by several types of medical professionals:\n\n1. Doctors who commonly treat hemorrhoids:\n- Gastroenterologists\n- Proctologists (colorectal surgeons)\n- General surgeons\n- Primary care physicians\n\n2. Treatment options:\nMild cases:\n- Over-the-counter creams and ointments\n- Sitz baths\n- Dietary changes\n- Increased fiber intake\n- Topical pain relievers\n\nModerate to severe cases:\n- Rubber band ligation\n- Sclerotherapy\n- Infrared coagulation\n- Hemorrhoidectomy (surgical removal)\n\n3. At-home management:\n- Use soft toilet paper\n- Keep area clean\n- Apply cold compresses\n- Avoid straining during bowel movements\n- Stay hydrated\n- Exercise regularly\n\n4. When to see a doctor:\n- Persistent bleeding\n- Severe pain\n- Large hemorrhoids\n- No improvement with home treatment\n- Frequent recurrence\n\nThe specific treatment depends on the severity and type of hemorrhoids. A healthcare professional can provide the most appropriate treatment plan.",
